"{\"uid\": \"newseu.cgtn.com-news-2024-04-16-What-is-the-Olympic-torch-and-what-does-it-symbolize--1sP8nbKahkQ-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael Marillier in London  Copied  WATCH: The lowdown on the Paris 2024 torch  The world's top athletes will be aiming to leave the Paris Olympics in a blaze of glory.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 226, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999951896825, \"rank\": 2.7719532898136045e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 268, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.940389442793096e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it all starts with a single flame.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic torch takes center stage on Tuesday, as the symbolic relay begins in the Greek town of Olympia.\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 418, \"end\": 431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.27200279502087e-21, \"text\": \"Olympic torch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}, {\"begin\": 499, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greektown\", \"score\": 0.9999999950587153, \"rank\": 4.941196422005916e-09, \"text\": \"Greek town\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greektown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greektown\"}, {\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.9999463214945655, \"rank\": 5.3681387197015664e-05, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch will carry a flame all the way to Paris and will play a starring role in the opening ceremony on July 26.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9700840135992408e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lighting of the Olympic cauldron marks the official start of the Games.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then it's time for some red-hot sporting action.\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are seven things you may not know about the torch at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 torch will light the Olympic cauldron at the opening ceremony of the Games./Paris 2024  1.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.940389442793096e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A big deal in a small package  The Paris 2024 torch stands 70 centimeters tall and weighs around 1.5 kilograms.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.940389442793096e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is not just one - the manufacturers will produce around 2,000 identical torches for the Games.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1158, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2.\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a piece of art  French artist Mathieu Lahanneurcame up with the design for the torch that will be used at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9960957824222564, \"rank\": 0.0038236513406217677, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lahanneur posted on his website, saying the project was \\\"a designer's dream: a dream that only comes true once in a lifetime, like a miraculous encounter with history.\\\"\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The curves of the Olympic torch reflect the themes of equality and peace /Paris 2024  3.\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not just about looks  The torch features several details that reflect the key values of Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1638, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.940389442793096e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers say its perfectly symmetrical shape is asymbol of equality.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1720, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The curves and rounded lines represent a call for peace and a more gentle world.\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then there is the 'ripple effect', a nod to the role that water will play at the Games.\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers have chosen to host the opening ceremony on the famous River Seine.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch relay will also cross several oceans, making stops at French territories around the world.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2039, \"end\": 2045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9960957824222564, \"rank\": 0.0038236513406217677, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Designer Mathieu Lahanneur says he wanted to build a torch that was 'extremely pure, iconic, and almost essential.\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2191, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'/Mathieu Lahanneur  4.\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a team effort!\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 11,000 people will take part in the relay that will deliver the torch from Olympia to Paris.\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2321, \"end\": 2328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.9999463214945655, \"rank\": 5.3681387197015664e-05, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}, {\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9700840135992408e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torchbearers represent the 'core tenets' of this year's Games - sport, communities and 'the collective.'\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers say the people representing 'the collective' are those who build a \\\"more inclusive, more sustainable, and fairer society.\\\"\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 volunteers perform a rehearsal for the Olympic torch relay in Troyes, France./Stephanie Lecocq/Reuters  5.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2657, \"end\": 2671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Troyes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Troyes, France\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Troyes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Troyes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will blaze a trail across France  The torch relay will span400 towns and cities in France, as well as six French territories: New Caledonia, Reunion Island, French Polynesia, Guadeloupe, Martinique and French Guiana.\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999341718343089, \"rank\": 6.458274836445974e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2788, \"end\": 2794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999341718343089, \"rank\": 6.458274836445974e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9960957824222564, \"rank\": 0.0038236513406217677, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2831, \"end\": 2844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.9369436464446797e-12, \"text\": \"New Caledonia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\"}, {\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u00e9union\", \"score\": 0.9999999983647285, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Reunion Island\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u00e9union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u00e9union\"}, {\"begin\": 2869, \"end\": 2878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9587112088125882, \"rank\": 0.043066974504663944, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 2907, \"end\": 2920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0426412558371743e-17, \"text\": \"French Guiana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\"}, {\"begin\": 2907, \"end\": 2920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0426412558371743e-17, \"text\": \"French Guiana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch will head from Olympia to Athens before crossing the Mediterranean and arriving in Marseille.\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 3026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2948, \"end\": 2955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.9999463214945655, \"rank\": 5.3681387197015664e-05, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}, {\"begin\": 2959, \"end\": 2965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9999542107440756, \"rank\": 4.579134791353115e-05, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999997166924, \"rank\": 2.8334622815670764e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is plenty of symbolism in that journey - the French port was founded by Greek settlers more than 2,600 years ago.\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3078, \"end\": 3084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9960957824222564, \"rank\": 0.0038236513406217677, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3105, \"end\": 3110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.6263418048522916, \"rank\": 0.5844330208286325, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French leg of the relay will start on May 8.\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3152, \"end\": 3158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9960957824222564, \"rank\": 0.0038236513406217677, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch will then travel across France and its overseas territories ahead of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3231, \"end\": 3237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999341718343089, \"rank\": 6.458274836445974e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"6.\", \"from\": 3301, \"to\": 3303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tradition spans nearly 80 years  The Paris 2024 torch will be the twenty-first edition.\", \"from\": 3304, \"to\": 3395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3345, \"end\": 3355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.940389442793096e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Berlin was the first host city to hold an Olympic torch relay.\", \"from\": 3396, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3396, \"end\": 3402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9999989146223448, \"rank\": 7.578509939549278e-07, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was in 1936, and organizers have commissioned a new torch for every Summer Olympics since then.\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"7.The torch connects the Olympics and Paralympics  The torch will also feature at the Paralympic Games, which begin in Paris on August 28.\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3682, \"end\": 3687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9700840135992408e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be lit in England's Stoke Mandeville, the so-called birthplace of the Paralympics.\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3720, \"end\": 3727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.5504941767600678, \"rank\": 0.8165384835239551, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 3730, \"end\": 3746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stoke_Mandeville\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.972001041734771e-15, \"text\": \"Stoke Mandeville\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stoke_Mandeville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stoke_Mandeville\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A group of British athletes willtravel through the Channel Tunnel, handing over the torch to\\u00a0their French counterparts at a meeting point roughly halfway between France and the United Kingdom.\", \"from\": 3793, \"to\": 3985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3844, \"end\": 3858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_Tunnel\", \"score\": 0.9999998131611566, \"rank\": 1.8683903291184072e-07, \"text\": \"Channel Tunnel\", \"types\": [\"Q1311958\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_Tunnel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_Tunnel\"}, {\"begin\": 3892, \"end\": 3898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9960957824222564, \"rank\": 0.0038236513406217677, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3955, \"end\": 3961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999341718343089, \"rank\": 6.458274836445974e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3970, \"end\": 3984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999890146684, \"rank\": 8.272754291287763e-09, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In total around 1,000 people will carry the torch between August 25-28.\", \"from\": 3987, \"to\": 4058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe toStoryboard: A weekly newsletterbringing you the best of CGTN every Friday  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\", \"from\": 4060, \"to\": 4407, \"entities\": []}]}"